{"id": "duc04-testb-6:12#37", "contents": "Hall's observations contrast with those of some visitors from the United Nations and other organizations, who reported that the food situation seemed slightly better than a year or two ago. However, Hall noted that this assessment may be based on visits to the capital city of Pyongyang, where life appears to be slightly better. In rural areas, where foreigners are rarely allowed to visit, the situation is worse than ever. Hall also reported a decline in public healthcare, citing a hospital where surgeons performed a stomach operation without electric lights or anesthesia."}
